race.comment: OENOLOGY (1) has tackled tougher races than this all prep and is struggling. Very fit and this step up in distance looks the right move. Has a big weight but with a soft run from the good draw he can feature prominently. WING NUT (8) ran a nice race at Taree two back in this grade carrying 1.5kgs more. Likes racing here and will find this easier than last time out when he failed in a Class 3. Can spring back to form without surprising. BARCELONA EXPRESS (2) came from near the tail to record an impressive win recently over 1300m at Armidale. Getting up in the weights but he should hold this form at only the fifth run of the campaign. KHANT FAIL (9) had been going great guns for new trainer Neil Godbolt until a last start failure over 1600m at Tuncurry. Freshened up and should give a good account. WILDERNESS STAR (5) is a bold front runner who has been going okay in better races. Will probably be hailed the winner at some stage.
